  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Execution Hour opens the Battlefleet Gothic novel line from the gun-decks of the Imperial Navy. As Abaddon's Twelfth Black Crusade rolls across the Gothic Sector, newly promoted Captain Leoten Sempter takes command of the cruiser Lord Solar Macharius and fights a desperate delaying war against traitor fleets, sacrificed worlds, and the Planet Killer. The action moves from engagement to engagement rather than trenchline to trenchline: signals traffic, void shields, evacuation orders, and command decisions under impossible pressure. A fleet-action war-story in grim rearguard key.",
